  "text": "Linkage analysis has revealed, in all CBA grown strains, a prevalence of O-3-linked Gal and O-4-linked GlcNAc residues in proportions of approximately 1 : 1. Based on previous knowledge on H. pylori cell-surface glycans [CITATION_1] , these structures belong to N-acetyllactos- [CITATION_2] . Low amounts (<5%) of other O-chain and corerelated residues have also been identified and assigned as shown in Table 2 .",
